leadership_approach|process_results_people_vision|application_1|1|Invite ownership before closure|Before you finalise a route, identify who needs to shape it, challenge it, or understand the trade-offs. This does not mean opening every decision endlessly. It means building ownership before the plan becomes too fixed to be shared.|people|review|leadership_approach::process_results_people_vision::application_1
leadership_approach|process_results_people_vision|application_2|2|Add meaning to the route|When you explain the route, add the reason it matters and the places where you want challenge. This keeps your clarity, but turns directive structure into shared confidence and gives people a clearer reason to commit.|vision|review|leadership_approach::process_results_people_vision::application_2
leadership_approach|process_results_people_vision|application_3|3|Use pressure checks|In pressure moments, keep the route clear but add two checks before action hardens. Ask who needs more context or support, and whether the immediate move still serves the longer direction. These checks make action more measured, not slower.|people|review|leadership_approach::process_results_people_vision::application_3
